message.en_US: This is it! This is our little area where we experiment with game modifications away from the public eye.
We're a small community, but we've got some really dedicated people here.
Feel free to make yourself at home. I'm going to get back to work on the \v[combat.name.penguin-heat]s and make them throw giant meteors!
Hey, I'm going to stick around with Lea if that's alright with you.
Sure, go on ahead without me. I'll be here if you need me.
Oh, let me mark my quest as completed. You were a big help back there.
Thanks!
So... \. I take it you're here for \c[1]cheat codes\c[0]?
[nods]
Spheromancer Lea!
Please tell me I did not just hear you correctly!
Because it sounded like you were thinking about \c[1]cheating\c[0]!
To think that after all this time...
All that devotion to justice...
You're just going to throw it all away!?
Oops...\. Heh heh.
Looks like his 'connection was lost', if you know what I mean.
Why?
Don't worry, it's not anything serious. He will be back soon enough.
There are always going to be people like that...
Anyway...\. I believe you were interested in some \c[1]cheat codes\c[0].
Heh heh heh...\. Alright then!
You will need to obtain the \c[3]\v[item.toggle-arcanelab-skill.name]\c[0] item so you can use custom skills.
It should be in the modding hideout somewhere. Make sure you get that first.
Follow me when you are ready.
Foolish Quadroguard!
We will never stray from the path of justice!
You should be ashamed of even suggesting something as vile as cheating!
Look buddy, it was just a hypothetical question.
No need for all of that bravado.
[shakes head]
Very well...\. If anyone asks, you never saw me here.
Hi!
Oh hello there again...
Girl who I have never met...
Look, don't come crying to me if you get in trouble or break your game.
Pleasure doing business with you. Enjoy your new "perks".
You ever seen a building like this before?
There aren't any buildings like it anywhere else in Crossworlds.
Earlier, we found these cool unused building textures in the game files.
And so we constructed this place using them.
Pretty cool, right?
Do you know why there is a building from \c[3]Ku'lero Temple\c[0] all the way out here?
We actually built this place long before the expansion came out.
Turns out, all the textures were already in the game files long ago.
And so we used those assets to build this place.
Pretty cool, right?
Hey, do you have any experience modding consumable items?
[shakes head]
Aww, thanks anyway.\. I'm trying to create a new consumable out of the food in these crates.
I'm trying to make a new item buff that turns your body into solid metal for huge defense.
Unfortunately, they are just outputting error messages. I'm not sure what is going wrong.
